ppaauussee() -- System Call (libc)

Wait for signal
#iinncclluuddee <uunniissttdd.hh>
iinntt ppaauussee()

ppaauussee()  suspends  execution  until the  process  receives  a signal.   The
awaited  signal  could  come  from  kkiillll(),  aallaarrmm(),  or  the  controlling
terminal.

_S_e_e _A_l_s_o
aallaarrmm(), kkiillll(), lliibbcc, ssiiggnnaall(), sslleeeepp(), uunniissttdd.hh
POSIX Standard, section 3.4.2
